#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code exactly k odd numbers wale subarrays count karta hai using:

Exact(k) = AtMost(k) - AtMost(k - 1)

1. helper(nums, k) count karta hai kitne subarrays me at most k odd numbers hain.
2. Sliding window use hoti hai:
   - right pointer se window expand karte hain
   - nums[right] % 2 se check karte hain ki current number odd hai ya nahi
3. Agar odd count k se zyada ho jaaye,
   to left pointer aage badha ke window shrink karte hain.
4. Har valid window ke liye
   (right - left + 1) subarrays add ho jaate hain.
5. Final answer:
   helper(k) - helper(k-1)

Main idea:
Exactly k odd count directly nikalna tough hota hai,
isliye pehle at most k aur at most k-1 nikaal ke difference lete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    
    public int helper(int[] nums, int k){
        if(k < 0) return 0;
        int left = 0;
        int right = 0;
        int cnt = 0;
        int sum = 0;

        while(right < nums.length){
            sum += (nums[right] % 2);

            while(sum > k){
                sum -= (nums[left] % 2);
                left++;
            }
            cnt += (right - left + 1);
            right++;
        }
        return cnt;
    }

    public int numberOfSubarrays(int[] nums, int k) {
        int val1 = helper(nums, k);
        int val2 = helper(nums, k-1);
        int result = val1 - val2;
        return result;
    }
}
